## 📊 Success Metrics (NEW)

### Baseline Metrics (Measure Before Implementation)
- **Call redo rate**: % of calls that require redial due to voice issues
- **Time to first successful call**: Average time from signup to first quality call
- **User confidence score**: Survey rating (1-5) on voice output quality
- **Calibration adoption**: % of eligible users who complete calibration (if we build it)

### Success Criteria (Define Before Writing Code)
- **Primary**: 20% reduction in call redo rate for users who calibrate
- **Secondary**: 15% increase in user confidence score post-calibration
- **Tertiary**: <5% drop-off rate during calibration flow
- **Guardrail**: Overall activation rate doesn't decrease >2%

### Telemetry Events (Track Impact)
- `calibration_started` - User enters calibration flow
- `calibration_completed` - User saves calibration config
- `calibration_skipped` - User opts out of calibration
- `first_call_quality` - User rates first call after calibration
- `call_redo` - User redials due to voice issues (compare calibrated vs non-calibrated)

